<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-73-0236 </DOCNO><TEXT>As a result of energy/economic crisis, the European Community has drawnup a series of guidelines over the past few years as a basis for energypolicy in member states. These guidelines are essentially: (1) reductionof the correlation between the rate of growth of energy consumption andof the GDP; (2) reduction of the contribution of oil to energy consumptionto a maximum of 40%; (3) incentives for the use of solid fuel and electricenergy; (4) incentives for the use of renewable energy sources with theaim of increasing their contribution to the Community energy supply;and (5) formulation of an energy price policy compatible with the realisationof these objectives.</TEXT></DOC>